# Final Report: STM32 Integration & SOLID Review

## 1. Overview of Changes

The STM32 integration has been refined to adhere to strict protocol standards and improve system stability. The system now correctly distinguishes between device-specific metrics and external sensor data.

### Key Improvements:
- **Protocol Separation**: 
  - `AVAILABLE` (0x05): Transmits Raspberry Pi system metrics (CPU, RAM, SoC Temperature, Uptime) every 5 seconds.
  - `META` (0x09): Transmits environment sensor data from STM32 (Temp, Humidity, Direction, Tilt, Light) in 5-point batches (approx. every 5 seconds).
- **Data Field Expansion**: Added `light` field to the STM32 parsing logic and batch data structure.
- **Real-time Monitoring**: Integrated [SystemResourceMonitor](file:///c:/Users/1-16/Desktop/SubCameraApp_refactory_260306_queue_sensor%20communicate_ai%20ingredient/SubCameraApp_refactory_260306_queue_sensor%20communicate_ai%20ingredient/src/system/SystemResourceMonitor.h#15-32) to fetch actual Linux system metrics instead of placeholder values.
- **Connection Stability**: Refactored [CommandServer](file:///c:/Users/1-16/Desktop/SubCameraApp_refactory_260306_queue_sensor%20communicate_ai%20ingredient/SubCameraApp_refactory_260306_queue_sensor%20communicate_ai%20ingredient/src/network/CommandServer.cpp#10-11) with a binary packet parser to resolve the fragmentation issues that caused "partial reads" and disconnects.
- **Thread Safety**: Applied mutexes (`uart_mu_`, `server_mu_`) to protect shared hardware and network resources.

